\par }{\b\i\f32 Background - }{\f32 
\par }\tab The Knights Panther possess a long and illustrious history, tracing their founding \tab back to 1500 I.C. when they formed (as the Knights Rampant) to fight in the \tab 
crusades against Araby. They renamed their Order after the beasts they found in the \tab Sultan of Araby\rquote s palace in Istranbul. They gained fame again under the banner of \tab Magnus the Pious to fight the Incursions of Chaos. They se
rved in Nuln until \tab Magnus brother Gunthar withdrew to Middenheim after being refused the title of \tab Emperor. The Order saw the appointment of Count Leopold of Stirland as a grave \tab mistake and withdrew with Gunthar to Middenheim.
\par \tab They hone their skills by making regular mutant hunting forays into the nearby \tab Drak Wald Forest.
\par \tab On these hunts they are often accompanied by Templars of the White Wolf, and \tab as a \tab result the relations between the two Orders are friendly (but still competitive).
\par \tab Unlike many Orders they have no disdain of fighting on foot, where they use the \tab halberd to deadly effect.{\f32 
\par \tab 
\par }{\b\i\f32 Base of Operations -}{\f32  }The majority (90) of the Knights Panther are stationed in Middenheim, \tab but an additional contingent of 30 is based in Talabheim with the express permission \tab of Grand Duke von Krieglitz.{\f32 
