\par }{\b\i\f51 Background -}{\b\i\f51\fs28  
\par \tab }Not all knightly Orders are dedicated to a realm, or for that matter, anything of \tab worth. The Knights of the Golden Crest is essentially a club for wealthy men that \tab 
fancy themselves as warriors of reknown. Although only open to nobility, admittance \tab is by invite only (and a bribe is the usual method of gaining such an invite). \tab 
Supposedly, the Crests only ask the most deserving and skilled warriors to join, but \tab in practice an invalid could join with enough passed Crowns. 
\par \tab This was not always the case however. Indeed, the Order has a long and proud \tab history of heroic battles, and accounted themselves well during the last Incursions of \tab Chaos. At the palace in Altdorf 
lay the many banners of their fallen foes. The last \tab time the Order engaged in battle (without retainers and mercenaries) was well over \tab forty years ago, in a skirmish against the Tzeentch cult \lquote Changers of Fate\rquote , which \tab 
cost them many of their members. Since then, the Order has avoided the field of \tab battle and stuck to jousts and tourneys, but with their high failure rate they are \tab declining to enter many contests. Why the change? (see notes). The cause is \tab 
probably lost to history.
\par 
\par {\b\i\f51 Base of Operations -} 
\par \tab The Golden Crests have strongholds (mansions) at many locations, with \tab the biggest \tab located in Altdorf. They also have a sizeable stronghold in Talabheim.
\par 
