\par \pard \qj\widctlpar \tab Being openly arrogant, scornful of the lower classes, and obviously lacking in the \tab \lquote right stuff\rquote , the Crests have earned the disdain of commoners and other knightly \tab 
Orders alike. They are viewed as fashionable among the young noble set but have \tab spurned a few \lquote lesser nobles\rquote  and earned their enmity as well. Few would care to \tab 
voice these opinions openly, for the Crests wield considerable political clout.
\par \tab This political potency makes them difficult foes or neutral parties to deal with.
\par 
\par {\b\i\f51 Typical Attitude -} 
\par 
\par \pard \qj\fi1276\widctlpar {\i \lquote Get out of my way you insignificant oik, before I have you flogged!\rquote 
\par  - }Adelbert the Gifted (Golden Crest addressing a commoner).
\par 
\par \pard \qj\widctlpar \tab Their reputation proceeds them, and what\rquote s more, it is very accurate. They are \tab arrogant, scornful and self important. They are also lazy, and few train for any real \tab 
amount of time. Parties and social life are their mainstay. They ensure their members \tab get the best breaks from the government and social groups, and are also rumoured to \tab have links to the underground, being able to locate and retrieve items of 
\lquote special\rquote  \tab interest.
\par 
