\par }{\b\i\f32 Background - 
\par }\tab The Templars of the White Wolf can trace their heritage back further than just about any Order, right back to when they were a group of Ulrican mercenary Teutognens under the banner of Artur (approx -50 I.C).
\par \tab As time has gone by the Order has gradually evolved and the barbarian warrior has been replaced by the knight as the epitome of personal combat.
\par \tab The Templars of the White Wolf hone their skills by constant combat drills and matches at the temple, and regularly accompany the Knights Panther on their mutant hunting forays.
\par 
